---
import PageLayout from '../layouts/PageLayout.astro';
---

<PageLayout
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="Signal to Summit privacy policy and SMS terms and conditions."
>
  <section class="py-20 md:py-28">
    <div class="mx-auto w-full max-w-[45rem] px-6">
      <h1 class="text-summit-navy mb-8">Privacy Policy</h1>

      <div class="prose-privacy text-summit-navy/80 leading-relaxed space-y-6">
        <p>
          Signal to Summit LLC ("we," "us," or "our") respects your privacy and is committed to protecting your personal information. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and safeguard information when you visit signaltosummit.com or engage with our services.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-summit-navy text-xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">Information We Collect</h2>
        <p>
          We collect information you provide directly, including your name, email address, company, role, and message when you submit our contact form or subscribe to Summit Signals. We also collect standard web analytics data through Vercel Web Analytics, including page views, referral sources, and geographic data. This data is aggregated and does not identify individual visitors.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-summit-navy text-xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">How We Use Your Information</h2>
        <p>
          We use contact form submissions to evaluate potential advisory engagements and respond to your inquiry. We use email subscriptions to notify you when new Summit Signals content is published. We use analytics data to understand how visitors interact with our site and improve the experience.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-summit-navy text-xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">Data Storage and Security</h2>
        <p>
          Contact form submissions are stored in a private database accessible only to Signal to Summit. Email addresses are stored securely and never shared with third parties. We do not sell, rent, or trade your personal information to anyone.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-summit-navy text-xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">Email Communications</h2>
        <p>
          If you subscribe to Summit Signals, you will receive email notifications when new content is published. Every email includes an unsubscribe link. You can opt out at any time. We do not send promotional emails beyond content notifications unless you specifically request them.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-summit-navy text-xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">Cookies and Tracking</h2>
        <p>
          signaltosummit.com uses Vercel Web Analytics, which does not use cookies and does not track individual visitors across sites. We do not use third-party advertising trackers, remarketing pixels, or social media tracking scripts.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-summit-navy text-xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">Third-Party Services</h2>
        <p>
          Our site is hosted on Vercel. Videos are embedded from YouTube using privacy-enhanced mode. We use Resend for transactional email delivery. These services have their own privacy policies governing their handling of data.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-summit-navy text-xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">Your Rights</h2>
        <p>
          You have the right to request access to, correction of, or deletion of your personal information. To make such a request, contact us at the email address below.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-summit-navy text-xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">Contact</h2>
        <p>
          For privacy-related inquiries, contact Signal to Summit LLC at <a href="mailto:jaiah@signaltosummit.com" class="text-signal-blue-dark hover:text-signal-blue transition-colors underline">jaiah@signaltosummit.com</a>.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-summit-navy text-xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">Changes to This Policy</h2>
        <p>
          We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Changes will be posted on this page with an updated effective date.
        </p>

        <p class="text-summit-navy/50 text-sm mt-8">
          Effective date: March 2026
        </p>

        <hr class="border-summit-navy/10 my-12" />

        <h2 class="text-summit-navy text-2xl font-bold mb-8" id="sms-terms">SMS Terms & Conditions</h2>

        <p>
          Signal to Summit LLC does not currently operate an SMS messaging program. If SMS communications are introduced in the future, this section will be updated with applicable terms and conditions, including opt-in/opt-out procedures, message frequency, and carrier information.
        </p>

        <p class="text-summit-navy/50 text-sm mt-8">
          Last updated: March 2026
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</PageLayout>
